CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1959, pg. 12, reads: "Love's Labor's Lost...Sometimes Home is Where the Heart Remains - Sold for $1200 - Thirty-five years ago, Hezekiah Anderson stepped up to give $1,000 toward the construction of the present Centre Ave. YMCA. Mr. Anderson left most of his property to a daughter in Detroit.  The above house at 14 Watt St. was sold for $1200."
TitMainTitle: Two story house with brick asphalt siding, and child looking out second story window, 14 Watt Street, Hill District
